{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775858324833,"sessionID":"ses_28698b365ffe7Q6RX8YJsvujiT","part":{"id":"prt_d79678a3c0016v8eBnZ2H5j5Nw","messageID":"msg_d79676bd2001DF1fYgyOmf4z70","sessionID":"ses_28698b365ffe7Q6RX8YJsvujiT","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-1e9103cec80649cb82123f10fe1df472","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-013/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-013/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-013 — Redis 存储实现 Proposal\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Implement Redis and Valkey storage backends for AgentCube session management, providing high-performance, persistent storage with dual-provider support. This implementation provides:\n6: \n7: 1. **Dual Backend Support**: Redis (`go-redis/v9`) and Valkey (`valkey-go`) implementations selectable via `STORE_TYPE`\n8: 2. **Session Metadata Persistence**: Store `SandboxInfo` JSON documents keyed by session ID\n9: 3. **GC Indexes**: Sorted sets for expiry-based and last-activity-based garbage collection queries\n10: 4. **Singleton Pattern**: Thread-safe initialization via `sync.Once` with klog fatal on failure\n11: 5. **Atomic Operations**: Pipeline/multi-command batching for store/delete operations\n12: 6. **Graceful Error Handling**: `ErrNotFound` sentinel for missing session keys\n13: \n14: ## Scope\n15: \n16: ### In Scope\n17: \n18: | Deliverable | Description |\n19: |-------------|-------------|\n20: | `pkg/store/store.go` | `Store` interface with 9 methods: Ping, GetSandboxBySessionID, StoreSandbox, UpdateSandbox, DeleteSandboxBySessionID, ListExpiredSandboxes, ListInactiveSandboxes, UpdateSessionLastActivity, Close |\n21: | `pkg/store/singleton.go` | Provider constants (`redis`, `valkey`), `Storage()` singleton accessor, `initStore()` initialization logic |\n22: | `pkg/store/store_redis.go` | `redisStore` struct implementing `Store` interface using `go-redis/v9` |\n23: | `pkg/store/store_valkey.go` | `valkeyStore` struct implementing `Store` interface using `valkey-go` |\n24: | `pkg/store/doc.go` | Package documentation |\n25: | `pkg/store/store_test.go` | Unit tests for interface compliance, error handling, edge cases |\n26: \n27: ### Key Components\n28: \n29: ```\n30: pkg/store/\n31: ├── Store interface (store.go)\n32: │   ├── Ping(ctx) error\n33: │   ├── GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID) (*SandboxInfo, error)\n34: │   ├── StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox) error — SETNX + ZADD expiry + ZADD activity (pipeline)\n35: │   ├── UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox) error — SET XX only\n36: │   ├── DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID) error — DEL + ZREM (pipeline)\n37: │   ├── ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit) ([]*SandboxInfo, error)\n38: │   ├── ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit) ([]*SandboxInfo, error)\n39: │   ├── UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID, at) error\n40: │   └── Close() error\n41: │\n42: ├── Errors (store.go)\n43: │   └── ErrNotFound = errors.New(\"store: not found\")\n44: │\n45: ├── Singleton (singleton.go)\n46: │   ├── redisStoreType = \"redis\"\n47: │   ├── valkeyStoreType = \"valkey\"\n48: │   ├── initStoreOnce = sync.Once{}\n49: │   ├── provider Store\n50: │   ├── Storage() Store → initStoreOnce.Do(initStore)\n51: │   └── initStore() error → reads STORE_TYPE, builds provider\n52: │\n53: ├── Redis Implementation (store_redis.go)\n54: │   ├── redisStore struct\n55: │   │   ├── cli *redisv9.Client\n56: │   │   ├── sessionPrefix = \"session:\"\n57: │   │   ├── expiryIndexKey = \"session:expiry\"\n58: │   │   └── lastActivityIndexKey = \"session:last_activity\"\n59: │   ├── Environment: REDIS_ADDR, REDIS_PASSWORD, REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\n60: │   └── Commands: PING, GET, SETNX, SET XX, DEL, ZADD, ZREM, ZRANGEBYSCORE\n61: │\n62: ├── Valkey Implementation (store_valkey.go)\n63: │   ├── valkeyStore struct\n64: │   │   ├── cli valkey.Client\n65: │   │   ├── Same key constants as Redis\n66: │   ├── Environment: VALKEY_ADDR (comma-separated), VALKEY_PASSWORD, VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED, VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE, VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE\n67: │   └── API: B().Ping(), B().Get(), DoMulti (SETNX/ZADD/ZADD), SET XX, Zrangebyscore, Mget\n68: │\n69: └── Test Coverage (store_test.go)\n70:     ├── Ping connectivity\n71:     ├── CRUD operations\n72:     ├── ZSET index operations\n73:     ├── ErrNotFound scenarios\n74:     ├── Nil/zero validation\n75:     ├── Missing key tolerance in List*\n76:     ├── Singleton initialization\n77: ```\n78: \n79: ### Out of Scope\n80: \n81: - Redis Cluster deployment (single-node focus; Valkey supports comma-separated addresses)\n82: - Distributed lock implementation\n83: - Cache preheating strategy\n84: - Data migration tools\n85: - Redis Sentinel support\n86: - Session data encryption\n87: - Rate limiting on storage operations\n88: - Watch/subscribe for real-time updates\n89: \n90: ## Impact Analysis\n91: \n92: ### Upstream Dependencies\n93: \n94: | Dependency | Impact |\n95: |------------|--------|\n96: | `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` | Redis client library — Redis implementation |\n97: | `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | Valkey client library — Valkey implementation |\n98: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Logging singleton init failure |\n99: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | `SandboxInfo` struct definition |\n100: | `context` | Operation timeout/cancellation support |\n101: | `encoding/json` | SandboxInfo serialization |\n102: | `time` | Timestamp handling for expiry/activity |\n103: | `sync` | Singleton initialization guard |\n104: \n105: ### Downstream Consumers\n106: \n107: | Consumer | Usage |\n108: |----------|-------|\n109: | Session Manager (`pkg/router/session_manager.go`) | Query/create/update sessions via `Storage()` |\n110: | Router (`pkg/router/server.go`) | Session lookup for request routing |\n111: | Workload Manager (`pkg/workloadmanager/`) | Create sandbox → `StoreSandbox`; delete → `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` |\n112: | Garbage Collector (`pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go`) | `ListExpiredSandboxes` / `ListInactiveSandboxes` for cleanup |\n113: \n114: ### Breaking Change Considerations\n115: \n116: - **Store Interface Signature**: Adding/removing methods requires all implementations to update\n117: - **Key Pattern Changes**: Changing `session:` prefix or ZSET keys breaks existing data\n118: - **Environment Variable Names**: Rename requires deployment updates\n119: - **ErrNotFound Message**: Changing `store: not found` message breaks error comparison\n120: - **SandboxInfo Fields**: Missing JSON tags or new fields affect stored documents\n121: - **Singleton Fatal Behavior**: `klog.Fatalf` on init failure crashes process; must handle env validation before production\n122: \n123: ## Alternatives Considered\n124: \n125: ### Alternative 1: Single Redis Backend Only\n126: \n127: **Approach**: Implement only Redis, skip Valkey support.\n128: \n129: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n130: |--------|------------|\n131: | Pros | Simpler codebase; single dependency; fewer tests |\n132: | Cons | Locks into Redis vendor; Valkey is open-source Redis alternative with better licensing; limits deployment flexibility |\n133: \n134: **Decision**: Rejected. Valkey is LF-supported Redis fork; dual support provides vendor flexibility without significant complexity overhead (same data model, similar APIs).\n135: \n136: ### Alternative 2: In-Memory Storage\n137: \n138: **Approach**: Use `sync.Map` or map with mutex for in-memory storage.\n139: \n140: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n141: |--------|------------|\n142: | Pros | No external dependency; simpler deployment; fast local access |\n143: | Cons | No persistence (restart loses data); no distributed access; no GC indexes without custom implementation |\n144: \n145: **Decision**: Rejected. Production requires persistence for session continuity across restarts and distributed access for multi-instance deployment.\n146: \n147: ### Alternative 3: Etcd Storage\n148: \n149: **Approach**: Use Etcd as storage backend.\n150: \n151: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n152: |--------|------------|\n153: | Pros | Strong consistency; Kubernetes-native; built-in watch/lease |\n154: | Cons | Higher latency than Redis/Valkey; heavier resource footprint; overkill for session metadata |\n155: \n156: **Decision**: Rejected. Session storage prioritizes low-latency reads/writes over strong consistency. Redis/Valkey sorted sets provide efficient expiry/activity queries.\n157: \n158: ### Alternative 4: Database Storage (PostgreSQL/MySQL)\n159: \n160: **Approach**: Use relational database with session table and indexed columns.\n161: \n162: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n163: |--------|------------|\n164: | Pros | Strong consistency; familiar SQL queries; existing DB infrastructure |\n165: | Cons | Higher latency; heavier for simple key-value patterns; connection pool complexity |\n166: \n167: **Decision**: Rejected. Session data is simple key-value with time-based queries. Redis/Valkey sorted sets are optimal for `ZRANGEBYSCORE` expiry/inactivity lookups.\n168: \n169: ### Alternative 5: Pipeline vs. Individual Commands\n170: \n171: **Approach**: Execute `StoreSandbox` and `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` as separate commands without pipeline.\n172: \n173: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n174: |--------|------------|\n175: | Pros | Simpler code; easier error handling per command |\n176: | Cons | Multiple round trips; partial success leaves inconsistent state (key exists without ZSET entry) |\n177: \n178: **Decision**: Rejected. Pipeline/multi ensures atomic batch: all commands succeed or fail together, maintaining consistency between session key and ZSET indexes.\n179: \n180: ## Risks\n181: \n182: | Risk | Mitigation |\n183: |------|------------|\n184: | Redis/Valkey connection failure | Env validation on init; `Ping` for health check; singleton fatal catches early |\n185: | Missing password with required=true | Explicit check: `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` to disable |\n186: | ZSET orphan members (key deleted, ZSET entry remains) | `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` skips missing keys without error |\n187: | Key collision across namespaces | Key pattern `session:{sessionID}` uses globally unique session ID |\n188: | Pipeline partial failure | Redis pipeline returns all errors; Valkey `DoMulti` fails on any error |\n189: | Clock skew for expiry scoring | Unix timestamp scoring is absolute; relies on server clock accuracy |\n190: | Singleton race condition | `sync.Once` guarantees single initialization |\n191: | Valkey MGET slot requirement | Comment notes keys should be in same slot; deployment must ensure consistent hashing |\n192: \n193: ## Implementation Notes\n194: \n195: 1. **Key Pattern**: `session:{sessionID}` for JSON documents\n196: 2. **Expiry ZSET**: `session:expiry` — member = sessionID, score = `ExpiresAt.Unix()`\n197: 3. **Activity ZSET**: `session:last_activity` — member = sessionID, score = `at.Unix()` or `time.Now().Unix()`\n198: 4. **SETNX for Store**: Prevents duplicate session creation\n199: 5. **SET XX for Update**: Enforces key must exist before update\n200: 6. **ZRANGEBYSCORE**: `-inf` to `{before.Unix()}` for expiry/inactivity queries\n201: 7. **ErrNotFound**: Redis `redis.Nil` → `ErrNotFound`; Valkey `IsValkeyNil` → `ErrNotFound`\n202: 8. **STORE_TYPE**: Case-insensitive; defaults to `redis`; only `redis` or `valkey` accepted\n203: 9. **Password Required**: Default true; set `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` or `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` to disable\n204: 10. **Singleton Fatal**: `initStore` error → `klog.Fatalf(\"init store failed: %v\", err)`; process exits\n205: \n206: ## References\n207: \n208: - `session-store/design.md` — Detailed design specification\n209: - `session-store/spec.md` — Requirements and scenarios\n210: - `pkg/common/types/sandbox.go` — `SandboxInfo` struct definition\n211: - `deployment/client-go.md` — Kubernetes client reference\n212: - `changes/AR-012/proposal.md` — Related interface definition (if exists)\n213: - [go-redis v9](https://github.com/redis/go-redis)\n214: - [valkey-go](https://github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go)\n\n(End of file - total 214 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-013 — Redis 存储实现 Proposal\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement Redis and Valkey storage backends for AgentCube session management, providing high-performance, persistent storage with dual-provider support. This implementation provides:\n\n1. **Dual Backend Support**: Redis (`go-redis/v9`) and Valkey (`valkey-go`) implementations selectable via `STORE_TYPE`\n2. **Session Metadata Persistence**: Store `SandboxInfo` JSON documents keyed by session ID\n3. **GC Indexes**: Sorted sets for expiry-based and last-activity-based garbage collection queries\n4. **Singleton Pattern**: Thread-safe initialization via `sync.Once` with klog fatal on failure\n5. **Atomic Operations**: Pipeline/multi-command batching for store/delete operations\n6. **Graceful Error Handling**: `ErrNotFound` sentinel for missing session keys\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n| Deliverable | Description |\n|-------------|-------------|\n| `pkg/store/store.go` | `Store` interface with 9 methods: Ping, GetSandboxBySessionID, StoreSandbox, UpdateSandbox, DeleteSandboxBySessionID, ListExpiredSandboxes, ListInactiveSandboxes, UpdateSessionLastActivity, Close |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-013/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775858324804,"end":1775858324831}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775858324835,"sessionID":"ses_28698b365ffe7Q6RX8YJsvujiT","part":{"id":"prt_d79679166001SMoEU21CBU7gPI","messageID":"msg_d79676bd2001DF1fYgyOmf4z70","sessionID":"ses_28698b365ffe7Q6RX8YJsvujiT","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-bbfac2bd41764094a50727c83b4a8913","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-013/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-013/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-013 — Redis 存储实现 Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-013 — Redis 存储实现 |\n8: | Module | `pkg/store` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Stage | ST-1 |\n12: \n13: 实现 Redis/Valkey 存储后端，提供高性能的会话持久化能力，支持按过期时间和最后活跃时间索引以便垃圾回收。\n14: \n15: ## Architecture\n16: \n17: ```\n18: ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n19: │                      Application Layer                       │\n20: │                    (Session Manager, GC)                      │\n21: └────────────────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────┘\n22:                                  │\n23:                                  v\n24: ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n25: │                    Store Interface                            │\n26: │  Ping / GetSandboxBySessionID / StoreSandbox / UpdateSandbox│\n27: │  DeleteSandboxBySessionID / ListExpiredSandboxes            │\n28: │  ListInactiveSandboxes / UpdateSessionLastActivity / Close   │\n29: └────────────────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────┘\n30:                                  │\n31:               ┌──────────────────┴──────────────────┐\n32:               v                                     v\n33: ┌─────────────────────────┐           ┌─────────────────────────┐\n34: │     redisStore          │           │     valkeyStore         │\n35: │ (go-redis/v9 Client)    │           │ (valkey-go Client)      │\n36: └───────────┬─────────────┘           └───────────┬─────────────┘\n37:             v                                     v\n38: ┌─────────────────────────┐           ┌─────────────────────────┐\n39: │      Redis Server       │           │     Valkey Server       │\n40: │   (Single/Cluster)      │           │   (Single/Cluster)      │\n41: └─────────────────────────┘           └─────────────────────────┘\n42: ```\n43: \n44: ### Provider Selection\n45: \n46: ```\n47:                     ┌─────────────────┐\n48:                     │   Storage()     │\n49:                     │  (singleton)    │\n50:                     └────────┬────────┘\n51:                              │ initStoreOnce.Do(initStore)\n52:                              v\n53:                     ┌─────────────────┐\n54:                     │  STORE_TYPE?    │\n55:                     └────────┬────────┘\n56:                              │\n57:               ┌──────────────┼──────────────┐\n58:               v              v              v\n59:         \"redis\"         \"valkey\"        other/empty\n60:               │              │              │\n61:               v              v              v\n62:       ┌───────────┐  ┌───────────┐  ┌───────────────┐\n63:       │redisStore │  │valkeyStore│  │Error: invalid│\n64:       └───────────┘  └───────────┘  │  provider     │\n65:                                     └───────────────┘\n66: ```\n67: \n68: ## Data Structures\n69: \n70: ### Store Interface\n71: \n72: ```go\n73: package store\n74: \n75: import (\n76:     \"context\"\n77:     \"time\"\n78: \n79:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\"\n80: )\n81: \n82: type Store interface {\n83:     Ping(ctx context.Context) error\n84:     GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n85:     StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n86:     UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n87:     DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n88:     ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n89:     ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n90:     UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n91:     Close() error\n92: }\n93: ```\n94: \n95: ### Errors\n96: \n97: ```go\n98: var ErrNotFound = errors.New(\"store: not found\")\n99: ```\n100: \n101: ### Provider Type Constants\n102: \n103: ```go\n104: const (\n105:     redisStoreType  string = \"redis\"\n106:     valkeyStoreType string = \"valkey\"\n107: )\n108: ```\n109: \n110: ### Redis Implementation\n111: \n112: ```go\n113: type redisStore struct {\n114:     cli                  *redisv9.Client\n115:     sessionPrefix        string\n116:     expiryIndexKey       string\n117:     lastActivityIndexKey string\n118: }\n119: ```\n120: \n121: ### Valkey Implementation\n122: \n123: ```go\n124: type valkeyStore struct {\n125:     cli                  valkey.Client\n126:     sessionPrefix        string\n127:     expiryIndexKey       string\n128:     lastActivityIndexKey string\n129: }\n130: ```\n131: \n132: ### Singleton\n133: \n134: ```go\n135: var (\n136:     initStoreOnce = &sync.Once{}\n137:     provider      Store\n138: )\n139: \n140: func Storage() Store {\n141:     initStoreOnce.Do(initStore)\n142:     return provider\n143: }\n144: ```\n145: \n146: ## Redis Key Design\n147: \n148: | Key Pattern | Type | Purpose |\n149: |-------------|------|---------|\n150: | `session:{id}` | String | JSON document storing SandboxInfo |\n151: | `session:expiry` | ZSET | Index of sessions by expiry timestamp (score = ExpiresAt Unix) |\n152: | `session:last_activity` | ZSET | Index of sessions by last activity (score = Unix timestamp) |\n153: \n154: ### Key Construction\n155: \n156: ```go\n157: func sessionKey(sessionID string) string {\n158:     return sessionPrefix + sessionID  // \"session:\" + id\n159: }\n160: ```\n161: \n162: ### Document Structure\n163: \n164: ```\n165: session:abc123 = {\n166:   \"kind\": \"AgentRuntime\",\n167:   \"sandboxId\": \"sb-456\",\n168:   \"sandboxNamespace\": \"default\",\n169:   \"sandboxName\": \"my-sandbox\",\n170:   \"name\": \"session-name\",\n171:   \"sessionId\": \"abc123\",\n172:   \"createdAt\": \"2024-01-01T00:00:00Z\",\n173:   \"expiresAt\": \"2024-01-02T00:00:00Z\",\n174:   \"status\": \"active\",\n175:   \"entryPoints\": [...],\n176:   \"userToken\": \"...\",\n177:   \"serviceAccount\": \"...\",\n178:   \"serviceAccountName\": \"...\"\n179: }\n180: ```\n181: \n182: ## API Contracts\n183: \n184: ### Ping\n185: \n186: ```go\n187: func (s *redisStore) Ping(ctx context.Context) error\n188: func (s *valkeyStore) Ping(ctx context.Context) error\n189: ```\n190: \n191: - Redis: `PING` command, expects `PONG` response\n192: - Valkey: `B().Ping().Build()`, expects `PONG` string\n193: \n194: ### GetSandboxBySessionID\n195: \n196: ```go\n197: func (s *redisStore) GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n198: func (s *valkeyStore) GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n199: ```\n200: \n201: - Redis: `GET session:{id}`, `redis.Nil` → `ErrNotFound`\n202: - Valkey: `B().Get().Key(key).Build()`, `IsValkeyNil` → `ErrNotFound`\n203: \n204: ### StoreSandbox\n205: \n206: ```go\n207: func (s *redisStore) StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n208: func (s *valkeyStore) StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n209: ```\n210: \n211: **Validation:**\n212: - Reject nil sandbox\n213: - Reject zero ExpiresAt\n214: \n215: **Atomic Operations (Pipeline/Multi):**\n216: 1. `SETNX session:{id} <json>` - Only create if not exists\n217: 2. `ZADD session:expiry {expiresAtUnix} {sessionID}` - Add to expiry index\n218: 3. `ZADD session:last_activity {nowUnix} {sessionID}` - Add to activity index\n219: \n220: **Returns:** Error if any command fails or session already exists\n221: \n222: ### UpdateSandbox\n223: \n224: ```go\n225: func (s *redisStore) UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n226: func (s *valkeyStore) UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n227: ```\n228: \n229: - Redis: `SET session:{id} <json> XX` (XX = only if exists)\n230: - Valkey: `B().Set().Key(key).Value(json).Build()` with existence check\n231: - Does NOT modify expiry or last_activity ZSETs\n232: - Returns error if key doesn't exist\n233: \n234: ### DeleteSandboxBySessionID\n235: \n236: ```go\n237: func (s *redisStore) DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n238: func (s *valkeyStore) DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n239: ```\n240: \n241: **Atomic Operations (Pipeline/Multi):**\n242: 1. `DEL session:{id}`\n243: 2. `ZREM session:expiry {sessionID}`\n244: 3. `ZREM session:last_activity {sessionID}`\n245: \n246: ### ListExpiredSandboxes\n247: \n248: ```go\n249: func (s *redisStore) ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n250: func (s *valkeyStore) ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n251: ```\n252: \n253: - If `limit <= 0`, returns `nil, nil`\n254: - `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:expiry -inf {before.Unix()} LIMIT 0 {limit}`\n255: - Pipeline GET for each session ID\n256: - Skips missing keys (orphan ZSET members)\n257: \n258: ### ListInactiveSandboxes\n259: \n260: ```go\n261: func (s *redisStore) ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n262: func (s *valkeyStore) ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n263: ```\n264: \n265: - Same logic as ListExpiredSandboxes but uses `session:last_activity` ZSET\n266: - `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:last_activity -inf {before.Unix()} LIMIT 0 {limit}`\n267: \n268: ### UpdateSessionLastActivity\n269: \n270: ```go\n271: func (s *redisStore) UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n272: func (s *valkeyStore) UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n273: ```\n274: \n275: **Validation:**\n276: - Reject empty sessionID\n277: - If `at` is zero, use `time.Now()`\n278: \n279: **Operations:**\n280: 1. Check if `session:{id}` exists\n281: 2. If not exists, return `ErrNotFound`\n282: 3. `ZADD session:last_activity {at.Unix()} {sessionID}`\n283: \n284: ### Close\n285: \n286: ```go\n287: func (s *redisStore) Close() error\n288: func (s *valkeyStore) Close() error\n289: ```\n290: \n291: - Close the underlying client connection\n292: \n293: ## Error Handling\n294: \n295: ### Custom Errors\n296: \n297: ```go\n298: var (\n299:     ErrNotFound              = errors.New(\"store: not found\")\n300:     ErrNilSandbox           = errors.New(\"store: sandbox is nil\")\n301:     ErrZeroExpiresAt        = errors.New(\"store: expiresAt is required\")\n302:     ErrEmptySessionID       = errors.New(\"store: sessionID is required\")\n303:     ErrInvalidProvider      = errors.New(\"store: invalid provider type\")\n304:     ErrPasswordRequired     = errors.New(\"store: password is required\")\n305:     ErrKeyNotExists        = errors.New(\"store: key not exists\")\n306: )\n307: ```\n308: \n309: ### Error Wrapping Examples\n310: \n311: ```go\n312: // Redis\n313: if err == redis.Nil {\n314:     return ErrNotFound\n315: }\n316: return fmt.Errorf(\"store: get session %s: %w\", sessionID, err)\n317: \n318: // Valkey\n319: if valkey.IsValkeyNil(resp) {\n320:     return nil, ErrNotFound\n321: }\n322: ```\n323: \n324: ## Configuration\n325: \n326: ### Environment Variables (Redis)\n327: \n328: | Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n329: |----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n330: | `STORE_TYPE` | No | `redis` | Provider type (`redis` or `valkey`) |\n331: | `REDIS_ADDR` | Yes | - | Redis address (e.g., `localhost:6379`) |\n332: | `REDIS_PASSWORD` | Conditional | - | Password (required unless `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`) |\n333: | `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` | No | `true` | Set to `false` to disable password requirement |\n334: \n335: ### Environment Variables (Valkey)\n336: \n337: | Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n338: |----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n339: | `STORE_TYPE` | Yes | - | Must be `valkey` |\n340: | `VALKEY_ADDR` | Yes | - | Comma-separated addresses |\n341: | `VALKEY_PASSWORD` | Conditional | - | Password (required unless `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`) |\n342: | `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` | No | `true` | Set to `false` to disable password requirement |\n343: | `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` | No | `false` | Set to `true` to disable client-side cache |\n344: | `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` | No | `false` | Set to `true` to force single client mode |\n345: \n346: ### Connection Options\n347: \n348: ```go\n349: // Redis\n350: func makeRedisOptions() (*redisv9.Options, error) {\n351:     addr := os.Getenv(\"REDIS_ADDR\")\n352:     if addr == \"\" {\n353:         return nil, errors.New(\"REDIS_ADDR is required\")\n354:     }\n355:     \n356:     password := os.Getenv(\"REDIS_PASSWORD\")\n357:     passwordRequired := strings.ToLower(os.Getenv(\"REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\"))\n358:     if password == \"\" && passwordRequired != \"false\" {\n359:         return nil, ErrPasswordRequired\n360:     }\n361:     \n362:     return &redisv9.Options{\n363:         Addr:     addr,\n364:         Password: password,\n365:     }, nil\n366: }\n367: \n368: // Valkey\n369: func makeValkeyOptions() (*valkey.ClientOption, error) {\n370:     addr := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_ADDR\")\n371:     if addr == \"\" {\n372:         return nil, errors.New(\"VALKEY_ADDR is required\")\n373:     }\n374:     \n375:     password := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD\")\n376:     passwordRequired := strings.ToLower(os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\"))\n377:     if password == \"\" && passwordRequired != \"false\" {\n378:         return nil, ErrPasswordRequired\n379:     }\n380:     \n381:     opts := &valkey.ClientOption{\n382:         InitAddress: strings.Split(addr, \",\"),\n383:         Password:    password,\n384:     }\n385:     \n386:     if v, _ := strconv.ParseBool(os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE\")); v {\n387:         opts.DisableCache = true\n388:     }\n389:     if v, _ := strconv.ParseBool(os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE\")); v {\n390:         opts.ForceSingleClient = true\n391:     }\n392:     \n393:     return opts, nil\n394: }\n395: ```\n396: \n397: ## Testing Strategy\n398: \n399: ### Unit Tests\n400: \n401: ```go\n402: // Using miniredis for Redis tests\n403: func TestRedisStore_StoreSandbox(t *testing.T) {\n404:     s := miniredis.RunT(t)\n405:     store := NewRedisStore(s.Addr(), \"\")\n406:     \n407:     // Test successful store\n408:     // Test duplicate store (SETNX behavior)\n409:     // Test nil sandbox rejection\n410:     // Test zero ExpiresAt rejection\n411: }\n412: \n413: // Using mocked valkey client for Valkey tests\n414: func TestValkeyStore_StoreSandbox(t *testing.T) {\n415:     // Test with mock client\n416: }\n417: ```\n418: \n419: ### Test Categories\n420: \n421: | Test Category | Description |\n422: |--------------|-------------|\n423: | Ping | Connectivity verification |\n424: | GetSandboxBySessionID | Found / not found |\n425: | StoreSandbox | Create new, reject duplicate, validation |\n426: | UpdateSandbox | Update existing, reject missing |\n427: | DeleteSandboxBySessionID | Remove all keys and ZSET members |\n428: | ListExpiredSandboxes | Query by expiry ZSET, handle missing docs |\n429: | ListInactiveSandboxes | Query by activity ZSET, handle missing docs |\n430: | UpdateSessionLastActivity | Check existence, update ZSET score |\n431: | Close | Clean shutdown |\n432: \n433: ### Integration Tests\n434: \n435: ```go\n436: func TestRedisStore_Integration(t *testing.T) {\n437:     if testing.Short() {\n438:         t.Skip(\"skipping integration test\")\n439:     }\n440:     \n441:     // Use real Redis or miniredis\n442:     // Verify end-to-end operations\n443:     // Test pipeline atomicity\n444: }\n445: ```\n446: \n447: ### Test Utilities\n448: \n449: ```go\n450: func setupTestRedis(t *testing.T) *redisStore {\n451:     mr := miniredis.RunT(t)\n452:     return &redisStore{\n453:         cli:                  redisv9.NewClient(&redisv9.Options{Addr: mr.Addr()}),\n454:         sessionPrefix:        \"session:\",\n455:         expiryIndexKey:       \"session:expiry\",\n456:         lastActivityIndexKey: \"session:last_activity\",\n457:     }\n458: }\n459: \n460: func makeTestSandbox(sessionID string) *types.SandboxInfo {\n461:     return &types.SandboxInfo{\n462:         Kind:             types.AgentRuntimeKind,\n463:         SandboxID:        \"sb-\" + sessionID,\n464:         SandboxNamespace: \"default\",\n465:         Name:             \"test-sandbox\",\n466:         SessionID:         sessionID,\n467:         CreatedAt:        time.Now(),\n468:         ExpiresAt:        time.Now().Add(24 * time.Hour),\n469:         Status:           \"active\",\n470:     }\n471: }\n472: ```\n473: \n474: ## File Structure\n475: \n476: ```\n477: pkg/store/\n478:   store.go           — Store interface, ErrNotFound, singleton access\n479:   store_redis.go    — redisStore implementation\n480:   store_valkey.go   — valkeyStore implementation\n481:   store_test.go     — Unit tests (using miniredis and mocks)\n482:   doc.go            — Package documentation\n483: ```\n484: \n485: ## Dependencies\n486: \n487: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n488: |---------|---------|---------|\n489: | `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` | latest | Redis client |\n490: | `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | latest | Valkey client |\n491: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | latest | Logging |\n492: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | local | SandboxInfo type |\n493: \n494: ## Performance Considerations\n495: \n496: ### Redis Implementation\n497: \n498: 1. **Pipeline for Atomicity**: StoreSandbox and DeleteSandboxBySessionID use pipelines to ensure atomic multi-key operations\n499: 2. **MGET for Batch Reads**: ListExpiredSandboxes/ListInactiveSandboxes can batch GET requests\n500: 3. **Connection Pooling**: go-redis manages connection pooling automatically\n501: \n502: ### Valkey Implementation\n503: \n504: 1. **DoMulti for Atomicity**: Similar to Redis pipeline\n505: 2. **Mget for Batch Reads**: Single MGET command for multiple session documents\n506: 3. **Client-Side Cache**: Optional `DisableCache` for memory-sensitive deployments\n507: \n508: ### Key Locality\n509: \n510: For Valkey cluster deployments, ensure session keys and ZSET keys map to the same slot by using hash tags:\n511: \n512: ```\n513: session:{sessionID}          → uses hash tag\n514: session:expiry               → no hash tag needed (single key)\n515: session:last_activity        → no hash tag needed (single key)\n516: ```\n517: \n518: Note: Current implementation assumes single-node or properly sharded deployment. For multi-node clusters, consider using hash tags for session IDs.\n519: \n520: ## Security Considerations\n521: \n522: 1. **Password Protection**: Password required by default, can be disabled for local development\n523: 2. **TLS Support**: Both go-redis and valkey-go support TLS connections (add via config)\n524: 3. **No Secrets in Logs**: Ensure session data with UserToken is not logged\n525: \n526: ## Migration Notes\n527: \n528: If migrating from a previous store implementation:\n529: \n530: 1. Data migration script to convert existing sessions to new JSON format\n531: 2. Rebuild ZSET indexes from existing session data\n532: 3. Run dual-write period during migration window\n533: \n534: ## References\n535: \n536: - AR-012 — 会话存储接口定义 (Store interface)\n537: - Redis Documentation: https://redis.io/docs/\n538: - go-redis Documentation: https://redis.uptrace.dev/\n539: - Valkey-go Documentation: https://github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go\n\n(End of file - total 539 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-013 — Redis 存储实现 Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-013 — Redis 存储实现 |\n| Module | `pkg/store` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\n实现 Redis/Valkey 存储后端，提供高性能的会话持久化能力，支持按过期时间和最后活跃时间索引以便垃圾回收。\n\n## Architecture\n\n```\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                      Application Layer                       │\n│                    (Session Manager, GC)                      │","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-013/design.md","time":{"start":1775858324809,"end":1775858324833}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775858324838,"sessionID":"ses_28698b365ffe7Q6RX8YJsvujiT","part":{"id":"prt_d796794e5001wvhaNIamOF4I3P","messageID":"msg_d79676bd2001DF1fYgyOmf4z70","sessionID":"ses_28698b365ffe7Q6RX8YJsvujiT","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-366bd4ef4a5f42b796b04dc3124c7adf","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-013/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-013/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-013 — Redis 存储实现 Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Metadata\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-013 — Redis 存储实现 |\n8: | Module | `pkg/store` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Task Checklist\n16: \n17: ### Phase 1: Dependencies Setup\n18: \n19: - [ ] **T1.1** Add Redis client dependency\n20:   - Run: `go get github.com/redis/go-redis/v9@latest`\n21:   - Update `go.mod` and `go.sum`\n22:   - Verify: `go mod tidy && go mod verify`\n23: \n24: - [ ] **T1.2** Add Valkey client dependency\n25:   - Run: `go get github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go@latest`\n26:   - Update `go.mod` and `go.sum`\n27:   - Verify: `go mod tidy && go mod verify`\n28: \n29: - [ ] **T1.3** Add test dependency (miniredis)\n30:   - Run: `go get github.com/alicebob/miniredis/v2@latest`\n31:   - Verify: `go mod tidy`\n32: \n33: - [ ] **T1.4** Verify pkg/common/types.SandboxInfo exists\n34:   - Check: `pkg/common/types/sandbox.go` has SandboxInfo struct\n35:   - Verify struct has required fields: Kind, SandboxID, SessionID, CreatedAt, ExpiresAt, Status, LastActivity\n36: \n37: ### Phase 2: Core Interface & Types\n38: \n39: - [ ] **T2.1** Create `pkg/store/doc.go`\n40:   - Add package documentation\n41:   - Describe store module purpose (Redis/Valkey session persistence)\n42:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n43: \n44: - [ ] **T2.2** Create `pkg/store/store.go` - Interface Definition\n45:   - Define `Store` interface with methods:\n46:     - `Ping(ctx) error`\n47:     - `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n48:     - `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox) error`\n49:     - `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox) error`\n50:     - `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID) error`\n51:     - `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n52:     - `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n53:     - `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID, at) error`\n54:     - `Close() error`\n55:   - Define `ErrNotFound = errors.New(\"store: not found\")`\n56:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n57: \n58: - [ ] **T2.3** Create `pkg/store/store.go` - Singleton Pattern\n59:   - Define `initStoreOnce sync.Once`\n60:   - Define `provider Store`\n61:   - Implement `Storage() Store` function\n62:   - Implement `initStore()` function\n63:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n64: \n65: - [ ] **T2.4** Create `pkg/store/store.go` - Error Types\n66:   - Define error constants:\n67:     - `ErrNotFound`\n68:     - `ErrNilSandbox`\n69:     - `ErrZeroExpiresAt`\n70:     - `ErrEmptySessionID`\n71:     - `ErrInvalidProvider`\n72:     - `ErrPasswordRequired`\n73:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n74: \n75: - [ ] **T2.5** Create `pkg/store/store.go` - Provider Type Constants\n76:   - Define constants:\n77:     - `redisStoreType = \"redis\"`\n78:     - `valkeyStoreType = \"valkey\"`\n79:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n80: \n81: ### Phase 3: Redis Implementation - Configuration\n82: \n83: - [ ] **T3.1** Create `pkg/store/store_redis.go` - Configuration Function\n84:   - Implement `makeRedisOptions() (*redisv9.Options, error)`\n85:   - Read `REDIS_ADDR` env var (required)\n86:   - Read `REDIS_PASSWORD` env var\n87:   - Read `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` env var (default: true)\n88:   - Validate: address required, password required unless explicitly disabled\n89:   - Return `redisv9.Options{Addr, Password}`\n90:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n91: \n92: - [ ] **T3.2** Create `pkg/store/store_redis.go` - Struct Definition\n93:   - Define `redisStore struct` with fields:\n94:     - `cli *redisv9.Client`\n95:     - `sessionPrefix string` (default: \"session:\")\n96:     - `expiryIndexKey string` (default: \"session:expiry\")\n97:     - `lastActivityIndexKey string` (default: \"session:last_activity\")\n98:   - Implement `NewRedisStore(addr, password string) (*redisStore, error)`\n99:   - Create client, set key prefixes\n100:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n101: \n102: - [ ] **T3.3** Implement helper function `sessionKey(sessionID string) string`\n103:   - Return `sessionPrefix + sessionID`\n104:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n105: \n106: ### Phase 4: Redis Implementation - Core Methods\n107: \n108: - [ ] **T4.1** Implement `Ping(ctx context.Context) error` for redisStore\n109:   - Execute `cli.Ping(ctx)`\n110:   - Expect `PONG` response\n111:   - Return error if ping fails\n112:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n113: \n114: - [ ] **T4.2** Implement `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)` for redisStore\n115:   - Build key: `sessionKey(sessionID)`\n116:   - Execute `cli.Get(ctx, key)`\n117:   - Handle `redis.Nil` → return `ErrNotFound`\n118:   - Unmarshal JSON to `types.SandboxInfo`\n119:   - Return sandbox and nil on success\n120:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n121: \n122: - [ ] **T4.3** Implement `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox) error` for redisStore - Part 1\n123:   - Validate: reject nil sandbox → return `ErrNilSandbox`\n124:   - Validate: reject zero ExpiresAt → return `ErrZeroExpiresAt`\n125:   - Marshal sandbox to JSON\n126:   - Build key: `sessionKey(sandbox.SessionID)`\n127:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n128: \n129: - [ ] **T4.4** Implement `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox) error` for redisStore - Part 2 (Pipeline)\n130:   - Create pipeline: `cli.Pipeline()`\n131:   - Execute `SETNX session:{id} <json>` (only create if not exists)\n132:   - Execute `ZADD session:expiry {expiresAtUnix} {sessionID}`\n133:   - Execute `ZADD session:last_activity {nowUnix} {sessionID}`\n134:   - Exec pipeline\n135:   - Return error if SETNX fails (session already exists) or any command fails\n136:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n137: \n138: - [ ] **T4.5** Implement `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox) error` for redisStore\n139:   - Validate: reject nil sandbox\n140:   - Marshal sandbox to JSON\n141:   - Build key: `sessionKey(sandbox.SessionID)`\n142:   - Execute `SET key value XX` (only if exists)\n143:   - Return error if key doesn't exist\n144:   - Note: Does NOT modify ZSETs (expiry, last_activity remain unchanged)\n145:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n146: \n147: - [ ] **T4.6** Implement `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID) error` for redisStore - Pipeline\n148:   - Create pipeline: `cli.Pipeline()`\n149:   - Execute `DEL session:{id}`\n150:   - Execute `ZREM session:expiry {sessionID}`\n151:   - Execute `ZREM session:last_activity {sessionID}`\n152:   - Exec pipeline\n153:   - Return error if any command fails\n154:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n155: \n156: - [ ] **T4.7** Implement `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)` for redisStore - Part 1\n157:   - If `limit <= 0`, return `nil, nil`\n158:   - Execute `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:expiry -inf {before.Unix()} LIMIT 0 {limit}`\n159:   - Get list of session IDs from result\n160:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n161: \n162: - [ ] **T4.8** Implement `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)` for redisStore - Part 2\n163:   - For each sessionID, execute `GET session:{id}`\n164:   - Pipeline GET requests for efficiency\n165:   - Skip missing keys (orphan ZSET members)\n166:   - Unmarshal each JSON to `types.SandboxInfo`\n167:   - Return slice of sandboxes\n168:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n169: \n170: - [ ] **T4.9** Implement `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)` for redisStore\n171:   - Same logic as T4.7-T4.8 but use `session:last_activity` ZSET\n172:   - Execute `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:last_activity -inf {before.Unix()} LIMIT 0 {limit}`\n173:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n174: \n175: - [ ] **T4.10** Implement `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID, at) error` for redisStore\n176:   - Validate: reject empty sessionID → return `ErrEmptySessionID`\n177:   - If `at` is zero, use `time.Now()`\n178:   - Build key: `sessionKey(sessionID)`\n179:   - Check if key exists: `cli.Exists(ctx, key)`\n180:   - If not exists, return `ErrNotFound`\n181:   - Execute `ZADD session:last_activity {at.Unix()} {sessionID}`\n182:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n183: \n184: - [ ] **T4.11** Implement `Close() error` for redisStore\n185:   - Execute `cli.Close()`\n186:   - Return error on failure\n187:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n188: \n189: ### Phase 5: Valkey Implementation - Configuration\n190: \n191: - [ ] **T5.1** Create `pkg/store/store_valkey.go` - Configuration Function\n192:   - Implement `makeValkeyOptions() (*valkey.ClientOption, error)`\n193:   - Read `VALKEY_ADDR` env var (required, comma-separated)\n194:   - Read `VALKEY_PASSWORD` env var\n195:   - Read `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` env var (default: true)\n196:   - Read `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` env var (optional)\n197:   - Read `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` env var (optional)\n198:   - Validate: address required, password required unless explicitly disabled\n199:   - Return `valkey.ClientOption` with InitAddress, Password, DisableCache, ForceSingleClient\n200:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n201: \n202: - [ ] **T5.2** Create `pkg/store/store_valkey.go` - Struct Definition\n203:   - Define `valkeyStore struct` with fields:\n204:     - `cli valkey.Client`\n205:     - `sessionPrefix string` (default: \"session:\")\n206:     - `expiryIndexKey string` (default: \"session:expiry\")\n207:     - `lastActivityIndexKey string` (default: \"session:last_activity\")\n208:   - Implement `NewValkeyStore(addr, password string) (*valkeyStore, error)`\n209:   - Create client using `valkey.NewClient()`, set key prefixes\n210:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n211: \n212: ### Phase 6: Valkey Implementation - Core Methods\n213: \n214: - [ ] **T6.1** Implement `Ping(ctx) error` for valkeyStore\n215:   - Build command: `B().Ping().Build()`\n216:   - Execute `cli.Do(ctx, cmd)`\n217:   - Expect `PONG` string response\n218:   - Return error if ping fails\n219:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n220: \n221: - [ ] **T6.2** Implement `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)` for valkeyStore\n222:   - Build key: `sessionKey(sessionID)`\n223:   - Build command: `B().Get().Key(key).Build()`\n224:   - Execute `cli.Do(ctx, cmd)`\n225:   - Check `valkey.IsValkeyNil(resp)` → return `ErrNotFound`\n226:   - Unmarshal JSON to `types.SandboxInfo`\n227:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n228: \n229: - [ ] **T6.3** Implement `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox) error` for valkeyStore - Validation & JSON\n230:   - Validate: reject nil sandbox → return `ErrNilSandbox`\n231:   - Validate: reject zero ExpiresAt → return `ErrZeroExpiresAt`\n232:   - Marshal sandbox to JSON\n233:   - Build key: `sessionKey(sandbox.SessionID)`\n234:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n235: \n236: - [ ] **T6.4** Implement `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox) error` for valkeyStore - DoMulti\n237:   - Build commands:\n238:     - `B().Setnx().Key(key).Value(json).Build()` (SETNX)\n239:     - `B().Zadd().Key(expiryIndexKey).Score(float64(expiresAtUnix)).Member(sessionID).Build()`\n240:     - `B().Zadd().Key(lastActivityIndexKey).Score(float64(nowUnix)).Member(sessionID).Build()`\n241:   - Execute `cli.DoMulti(ctx, cmds...)`\n242:   - Check SETNX result: if 0, session already exists → error\n243:   - Return error if any command fails\n244:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n245: \n246: - [ ] **T6.5** Implement `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox) error` for valkeyStore\n247:   - Validate: reject nil sandbox\n248:   - Marshal sandbox to JSON\n249:   - Build key: `sessionKey(sandbox.SessionID)`\n250:   - Check existence first: `B().Exists().Key(key).Build()`\n251:   - If not exists, return error\n252:   - Execute `B().Set().Key(key).Value(json).Build()`\n253:   - Note: Does NOT modify ZSETs\n254:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n255: \n256: - [ ] **T6.6** Implement `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID) error` for valkeyStore - DoMulti\n257:   - Build commands:\n258:     - `B().Del().Key(sessionKey(sessionID)).Build()`\n259:     - `B().Zrem().Key(expiryIndexKey).Member(sessionID).Build()`\n260:     - `B().Zrem().Key(lastActivityIndexKey).Member(sessionID).Build()`\n261:   - Execute `cli.DoMulti(ctx, cmds...)`\n262:   - Return error if any command fails\n263:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n264: \n265: - [ ] **T6.7** Implement `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)` for valkeyStore\n266:   - If `limit <= 0`, return `nil, nil`\n267:   - Build command: `B().Zrangebyscore().Key(expiryIndexKey).Min(\"-inf\").Max(strconv.FormatInt(before.Unix(), 10)).Limit(0, limit).Build()`\n268:   - Execute and get session IDs\n269:   - Build MGET command: `B().Mget().Keys(sessionKeys...).Build()`\n270:   - Skip missing keys (IsValkeyNil)\n271:   - Unmarshal each JSON to `types.SandboxInfo`\n272:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n273: \n274: - [ ] **T6.8** Implement `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)` for valkeyStore\n275:   - Same logic as T6.7 but use `lastActivityIndexKey`\n276:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n277: \n278: - [ ] **T6.9** Implement `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID, at) error` for valkeyStore\n279:   - Validate: reject empty sessionID\n280:   - If `at` is zero, use `time.Now()`\n281:   - Build key: `sessionKey(sessionID)`\n282:   - Check existence: `B().Exists().Key(key).Build()`\n283:   - If not exists, return `ErrNotFound`\n284:   - Build command: `B().Zadd().Key(lastActivityIndexKey).Score(float64(at.Unix())).Member(sessionID).Build()`\n285:   - Execute command\n286:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n287: \n288: - [ ] **T6.10** Implement `Close() error` for valkeyStore\n289:   - Execute `cli.Close()`\n290:   - Return error on failure\n291:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n292: \n293: ### Phase 7: initStore Implementation\n294: \n295: - [ ] **T7.1** Implement `initStore()` function - Provider Selection\n296:   - Read `STORE_TYPE` env var\n297:   - If \"redis\", call `initRedisStore()`\n298:   - If \"valkey\", call `initValkeyStore()`\n299:   - If empty or other, return `ErrInvalidProvider`\n300:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n301: \n302: - [ ] **T7.2** Implement `initRedisStore()` helper\n303:   - Call `makeRedisOptions()`\n304:   - Create Redis client: `redisv9.NewClient(opts)`\n305:   - Set provider to `&redisStore{cli: client, sessionPrefix: \"session:\", expiryIndexKey: \"session:expiry\", lastActivityIndexKey: \"session:last_activity\"}`\n306:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n307: \n308: - [ ] **T7.3** Implement `initValkeyStore()` helper\n309:   - Call `makeValkeyOptions()`\n310:   - Create Valkey client: `valkey.NewClient(opts)`\n311:   - Set provider to `&valkeyStore{cli: client, sessionPrefix: \"session:\", expiryIndexKey: \"session:expiry\", lastActivityIndexKey: \"session:last_activity\"}`\n312:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n313: \n314: ### Phase 8: Unit Tests - Redis Store\n315: \n316: - [ ] **T8.1** Create `pkg/store/store_redis_test.go` - Test Setup\n317:   - Create `setupTestRedisStore(t *testing.T) *redisStore` helper\n318:   - Use `miniredis.RunT(t)` for in-memory Redis\n319:   - Create `makeTestSandbox(sessionID string) *types.SandboxInfo` helper\n320:   - Verify: `go test ./pkg/store/... -v`\n321: \n322: - [ ] **T8.2** Test `Ping()` f